---
import PageHeading from "../components/page-heading.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/main.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About Me"
  description="I'm Claudio Caporro, an Engineering Manager at TeamSystem. Legacy-code tamer, AI evangelist, GitOps practitioner, and team grower."
>
  <section class="relative z-20 max-w-2xl mx-auto my-12 px-7 lg:px-0">
    <PageHeading
      title="About Me"
      description="Hello 👋 I'm an Engineering Manager and mix of legacy-code tamer and therapist for developers on the edge."
    />

    <img src="/assets/images/about.png" alt="Claudio Caporro" class="relative z-30 w-full my-10 rounded-xl" />

    <h2 class="mb-2 text-2xl font-bold dark:text-neutral-200">Who I am</h2>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      My name is Claudio Caporro and, on paper, I'm an Engineering Manager.
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      In reality, I'm a mix of legacy-code tamer and therapist for developers on the edge, staring at a user story with no details while I explain to stakeholders why that bug isn't a bug — it's a "feature."
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      By day, I lead development teams at a business unit at TeamSystem. By night… well, I sleep (a little. AI FOMO is real, so I study)
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      I'm a master of Buzzword-Jitsu: I use AI for pretty much everything, even to generate plausible excuses when things go sideways. I spend my days convincing the team that AI tools aren't just a way to make someone else write your code — they're a superpower. We experiment, standardize, and share practices that move the dev role from code writer to solution designer.
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      Everything has to be GitOps. I automate anything I can. Now, when something breaks, it does it in an elegant, observable, and traceable way.
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      I design disaster-recovery and business continuity systems that, in theory, should survive an alien invasion. In practice, I just hope they survive the next git push —force from the intern on Friday (kidding… pushing on Fridays is banned).
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      My mission is simple: ship projects, grow the team (with minimal psychological damage), and keep an aura of competence intact.
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg mb-4"
    >
      I collect acronyms and read very long documents so I can say "we're compliant," which is the corporate way of saying "the paperwork is fine — we'll see about the rest."
    </p>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg"
    >
      In the end, things work, the team puts up with me, and the company hasn't fired me yet. And that, folks, is the definition of success.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-2 text-2xl font-bold lg:mt-10 sm:mt-6 dark:text-neutral-200">Let's stay in touch</h2>
    <p
      class="text-sm leading-6 text-gray-600 dark:text-neutral-400 sm:leading-7 lg:leading-8 sm:text-base lg:text-lg"
    >
      If you want to stay updated on my work, follow me on <a
        href="https://linkedin.com/in/claudio-caporro"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-indigo-600 underline">LinkedIn</a
      >, read my articles on <a
        href="https://medium.com/@claudiocaporro"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-indigo-600 underline">Medium</a
      >, or contact me on <a
        href="https://t.me/zeerg"
        target="_blank"
        class="text-indigo-600 underline">Telegram</a
      >.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
